31/05/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Belgian Foreign Minister Karel De Gucht paid visits to Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro on Monday (30 May), holding a series of talks on the reform and EU integration processes in the region. In Zagreb, De Gucht voiced his country's support for efforts to start accession talks with the EU, assuring Croatian counterpart Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic that Belgium sees considerable progress. 
In Belgrade, De Gucht met with Serbia-Montenegro counterpart Vuk Draskovic, Serbian President Boris Tadic and Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic. Afterwards, De Gucht said he hoped Stabilisation and Association Agreement talks with Belgrade could begin by October. 
In other news, Croatian President Stipe Mesic visited Chisinau on Monday, for talks with Moldovan counterpart Vladimir Voronin. They discussed their countries' respective EU membership bids as well as bilateral relations. (HINA, HRT, Beta, Tanjug - 30/05/05)
